subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
In both fore- and hind wings, ScP relatively long, length between termination of ScP and proximal end of pterostigma twice shorter than length of pterostigma [this length slightly longer than length of pterostigma in 

S. baltica

]; pterostigma distinctively paler in proximal part, darker in distal part [somewhat darker proximally in 

S. exhibens

]; in hind wing, anterior trace of MP with three pectinate branches [two branches in 

S. exhibens

].
